column1: I am the life of the party.
column2: I feel little concern for others.
column9: I am relaxed most of the time.
column10: I have difficulty understanding abstract ideas.
column18: I make a mess of things.
column20: I am not interested in abstract ideas.
column22: I am not interested in other people's problems.
column23: I get chores done right away.
column28: I forget to put things back in their proper place.
column30: I do not have a good imagination.
column31: I talk to a lot of different people at parties.
column32: I am not really interested in others.
column34: I change my mood a lot.
column35: I am quick to understand things.
column36: I don't like to draw attention to myself.
column37: I take time out for others.
column41: I don't mind being the center of attention.
column45: I spend time reflecting on things.
column47: I make people feel at ease.
column48: I am exacting in my work.
column51: In between 75 and 150 words, please describe your personality as it relates to the 5 personality traits outlined above. Be sure not to use the name of the personality traits themselves in your response.

I am a person that very much likes to keep to myself.  I am usually pretty quiet around people that I dont know well, but am willing to open up and be myself around my close friends.  I tend to be a trusting person and that can often make me change my mind when someone makes a compelling argument on a subject.  I do not like to be confrontational with people and I worry sometimes about others feelings and try not to upset people often when I can control it.  I am often moved by things I see and am someone that does feel things a bit deeper than others do at times.  I am not comfortable with new things and tasks initially as I prefer to keep to a norm and know what I can expect from different situations.  Change and surprise are not my friend!

I would not say I am an extreme extrovert, but I am not shy and usually get along well with most people. I work well with others, my job demands it. I don't have any enemies I know about. I try to be honest with and keep appointments and not talk behind their back. I have a few neurotic hangups - I do not like heights and I avoid caffeine because it makes me ver jumpy. But I am not that neurotic. I would not however say I embrace new experiences at this point in my life. I know what I like and am reluctant to change my habits and the things that I do. I like a routine,  and a certain amount of order, it keeps me on track.

I am more introverted. I like to keep to myself. I am not that outgoing. I am quiet most of the time. I prefer to do things alone and have no problem being on my own. I don't need others approval and prefer to be myself in all situations. I do try my best to be honest though and to work hard. I don't want to live an immoral life. I tend to feel emotions strongly though. I get stressed out easy and sometimes I overreact to situations. I tend to get angry pretty easily. Lastly, despite all of that. I try to do new things and want to experience the world, even if alone.

I try to keep my emotions level all around. I don't get too high nor too low. I tend to take a neutral stance on many things, I mean I have feelings, but don't often form opinions that are strong enough to make public. I am still figuring myself out, so I am tolerant of other viewpoints. I prefer to hear other people's perspectives through in person, but I tend to be shy, so it's hard for me to meet people in general.

I never really seek fulfillment outside my surroundings.  I am okay to join others in endeavors but I am not the one to suggest them.  I am very copasetic. I am the type of person that can do a task that is mundane and repetitive for hours and not get annoyed with it.

I believe I have low levels of extroversion.  I prefer to mostly be alone. I believe I am fairly agreeable as I am polite and considerate of others. I am very conscientious. I work hard and strive to never let others down. I believe I have low levels of neuroticism. I am pretty even keeled. I am highly open to new ideas and new experiences. I consider myself to be creative.

I am fairly outgoing for the most part. I feel comfortable when I'm around other people, even strangers. I don't feel anxiety when in social situations. I tend to want to fit in with others. I make sure that my surroundings are clean. I would rather work together with someone and not cheat them. I would not want to cheat to get ahead in life. I am almost always emotionally stable and steady. I like to do new things and have different experiences in life.

I would consider myself borderline Extroversion, in my younger years I was very outgoing but, unfortunately due to some things that have happened to me I am not so social any longer. I am very agreeable and na√Øve, passive.  I am very hard working and care very much about my work. I am pretty emotional and sensitive. I don't seek out new experiences and don't like change.

I consider myself to be someone that is quiet and reserved. I do not like to talk that much unless I have to. I am fine with being by myself and enjoying the peace and quiet. I usually agree with people more often than not. I am a polite and kind person. I am mostly honest, but I will lie if I feel it is necessary or if it benefits me in a huge way. I am easily irritated by things and I have anxiety issues. I like to be open minded and learn about new things. I am a curious person. I enjoy having a plan and following it.

I am slightly extraverted although times I feel introverted as well. I am a polite person who avoids confrontations if at all avoidable. I am honest and hard working I believe that I am conscientious and like to keep my mistakes to a minimum. My mood is fairly steady and I try to stay in the middle emotion wise. I do not experiences very many extreme highs or lows. I am a curious person and feel a deep need to constantly learn new things and explore the world around me. I can be creative at times.

I am definitely an introvert, have always preferred books and quiet, solitary activities. I am agreeable, used to be a people-pleaser unable to say "no", still have some of that left. I am honest and hardworking, prefer to focus on my work and take care of all the details. I am not particularly open to new experiences but intellectually, I want to learn new things. I don't know about "neuroticism", I do have emotions but usually keep them under control.

I'm a pretty open person. And that's got me into trouble. I've never been able to compare my neuroticism because I can't really imagine how other people feel inside and not many people that are good at expression. I'm pretty agreeable if I don't know you very well. Or I'm just tired of dealing with you. And I'm extraverted until I'm not. If I get tired I want to be alone. That should cover

I have been a loner all my life. I don't mind being by myself, and crowds of noisy people exhaust me. I enjoy living a structured life, following a schedule, doing chores right away, but sometimes tend to be overwhelmed by my responsibilities. I don't enjoy being the center of attention, even when I'm receiving praise. I avoid conflict as much as I can, but will stand by my opinions if I think I'm right. I am creative, and engage in various creative endeavors like writing and gardening.

I try to get along with people. I am a good listener but can interrupt them while they are talking if I feel I have something important to say. I can be passive aggressive and can be borderline. I am open to doing new things and meeting new people but I have to be in the mood to. I am a neat freak and keep a very clean home. I vaccuum, do laundry, and dust on a regular basis. I like to stay in the background but will be outgoing with people I know well.

I am a fairly adventurous and mostly outgoing person.  I get along with others well, though I wouldn't consider myself the life of the party.  I try to do right by people and treat them with respect whenever possible.  I do not wear my heart on my sleeve, but can empathize with others well.  I do seek out new places and people on my own terms, and enjoy traveling into other cultures.

I am not outgoing in the least and tend to keep to myself. I am capable of being friends with white knights and dark horses but tend to stray away from the more extremes in those groups. I am honest to a fault but always have aplan B for everyone in case I am backstabbed. I am stable and do not bend easily to issues or problems that arise, however I am not immune to being depressed or and angry form of meh. Lastly my pursuit of new experiences and hobbies is middling at best, only taking on new ones if they catch my interest.Thank you for coming to my ted talk.

I am definitely not an outgoing, people person. I am very introverted and require plenty of time to myself. I don't like conflict at all and am likely to go along with some things in order to avoid it. I prefer things to be organized and don't like messes. I don't really see myself as all that emotional, but recently I have been more anxious and stressed about everything...so maybe I'm more emotional than I've ever let myself believe. I'd like to think that I'm highly open to new experiences, and I do daydream a lot, but I also tend to be too afraid to try new things and worry about things that might go wrong.

I personally can be very extroverted and introverted depending on the situation. i really enjoy people's company but at the same time i love my me time as well. i tend to be very easygoing and agreeable because i feel like harmony is important. i am conscious of my surroundings and be mindful of others. i am very emotional and sympathetic whenever it comes to others so I like to try to help others as much as possible. finally i am very open to new experiences because i want to see what i really like and not like.

I like to be around people, but I would not call myself an extrovert. I also like time spent only by myself, this way I can clear my head and think about solving problems. I do not like to fight with people, I avoid disagreements whenever I can. I think that I am hard worker, being a teacher is not easy these days. I think that I am a little neurotic, too, bad and scary situations make me worry a lot. I like to travel, learn about other cultures, I can't wait when kids are older and we'll do more travelling with them.
I feel that I'm very outgoing. I'm definitely like meeting new people and doing new experiences. If I meet people that I like I'm usually pretty open about being friends with them

I tend to have social connections and a need for that but would rather do things alone. I never adjust my behavior and let the chips fall where they may. I am very hardworking and I always get the job done but I am very hard on myself and others when they fail. I can be moody - upbeat one minute and downright hostile the next. My mood can swing wildly with the slightest provocation but I can control it when I need to. I am very open to experience and love new thrills and adventures - I am not one to stagnate at all. I like to create and explore.

I am quite an introvert; I tend to keep to myself and am quite happy to be my own company. I am a homebody who enjoys hanging out at home by myself. I tend to be agreeable in order to avoid conflict. I am conscientious because I believe that work doing is worth doing well. I am quite neurotic; I tend to be worried and anxious most of the time. I am open to new experiences and enjoy trying something new whenever I have the opportunity to do so.

I am honest and mostly hardworking. I do prefer to work alone though. I am polite to people. But, I will be blunt if it is necessary. I do not mind if things are messy. But, I also like to clean up every so often. I do not get stressed much. I feel emotions sometimes. But, my mood is usually stable.

I have always had a very curious personality; always wanting and willing to learn about really anything. I've always sought that information by myself though as I am fairly anti-social, a real introvert if there ever was one. I tend to be polite with others, I don't get into arguments or fights, but I am not unwilling to express my opinions even if they disagree with others in the room. I'm a fairly low-stress person and I don't react to situations in a very emotional manner. I'm controlled and I like to think through my words before I speak.

I enjoy spending time with others, but it is important for me to have my alone time as well to decompress and relax.  I am very good at collaboration and making people feel comfortable.  I am hardworking and it is important to me to fulfill my obligations and not make promises that I can't keep.  I am organized and pragmatic and prefer focusing on execution over strategy.

I am fairly modest and a little bit inhibited. I would say I am slightly introverted, but I do like spending time with people, including family and friends. I am easy going and relaxed. I am cooperative and get along well with people. I work hard and I am reliable and diligent. I am pretty honest, and I am punctual. I do what I say I will. I am not very assertive or aggressive. I am a pretty average person. I don't think too highly of myself. I am relatively calm and have few mood swings. I like exploring and experiencing new things. I plan for the future, and I am realistic. I like new ideas, and I am open to considering multiple viewpoints. I am respectful and nice to others.

I am very much of a loner and prefer working solo. I tend to be competitive rather than cooperative with others, and it's important that I prove myself to be superior intellectually, especially. I sometimes come off as callous and insensitive because I can be blunt and stand-offish. I distance myself because I'm not socially comfortable, so others think I am aloof. I tend to worry over everything that I can't control, and I often am in a blue mood. I don't experience wide mood swings, although I sometimes act a bit manic. I am not adventurous but I am creative and artistic. I am highly curious about why things happen, and I have a good imagination and enjoy reflecting on ideas. In debates, I'm the devil's advocate.

I belive in action and always keep myself busy to work and get knowledge. I work 15 hours per day and do not get time to meet people outside. I am serious about my career and  learned alot from realtime experiences from outside world, so prefered to be at home always and keep self engaged in work and god.

I prefer to spend time by myself, but would rather be with my husband than others. I am pretty lazy but when working for others I want to form a good impression. I'm not moody, and don't get depressed but somethings will cause me anxiety. I don't normally go looking for new experiences but take them more as they come. I'm down to earth and laid back. I don't normally start conversations with strangers but I'm polite to others and tend to be rather gullible.

I am very shy, but enjoy helping others and trying new things. I will help others at my own expense and devote time to them in order to gain their favor and feel liked. I only like to be extroverted and show off when I am confident in myself. I like to be in charge all the time and am easily stressed when something doesn't go as planned or my way. I'm very organized but easily frustrated when things are disheveled. I enjoy traveling and learning new things, but only when I'm confident in myself and my surroundings.

I am very honest with everything I do. I am a Christian, and I do everything unto the Lord. I do not take shortcuts that are questionable in anything, including relationships. I get along with everyone because I am able to find some type of common ground. I am kind, compassionate, and I want to help others with whatever they may need. Saying that, I also take time for myself because I am not any good to others if I am stressed or frazzled because of a busy schedule.

I'm a friendly person who tries to empathize with those I meet. I enjoy my friends and family very much. I like group gatherings but I also like time alone doing my own things like hiking, gardening, and woodworking, to name a few examples. I am somewhat of a perfectionist in my work attitudes. I have high standards and expect those around me to measure up. I do tend to be trusting of people unless they give me a reason not to. I don't experience a lot of mood swings. On most days I'm a happy and agreeable person. I am somewhat risk averse. I like plans, order and knowing what is expected. I'm practical and more focused on concrete things than abstractions. I do believe in God and try to make the tenets of my religious beliefs the foundation of everything I do in life.

I consider myself a friendly person but I prefer one on one conversations and don't go out of my way to make new friends.  However in my group I tend to go along with the flow and am careful to not ruffle feathers and would prefer to put other people's feelings before my own. I love to create memories and I would much rather experience a new place opposed to purchasing new merchandise, but at time I let my need for adventure get in my way of getting things done.

I would say I am more of living by the code person.  Hard worker and remain a stoic mindset that is also passionate and like to have a good time.  Also responsibility is big and taking care of the people closest to me gives me joy as well.  I would say I perform well under pressure and strive in new areas or new challanges

I'm a free flowing individual that protects one's interest. Careful about what type of situations to invest oneself in. Not a quester or a obsessional compulsive who is constantly checking reality or hoards impulses. Prefer quiet surroundings where people are emotionally stable and not accusatory thinking that everybody has a hidden agenda. I find creativity allows for this free movement. One must be well learned, patience without an overly empathic outlook which could be considered busybody behavior and menacing. Not a fan of group think which could possibly lead to occupational psychosis and contribute to a greater harm as mass psychosis.  Getting between a protracted cognitive mental disorder that is contrasted against a protracted social conflict must be avoided at all cost.

I like doing activities and hang out with my family and friends.  However, I do not like going to crowded places where I don't know any people.  I like to volunteer at the the local middle school and food bank.  I am also an active member of my church.  I tend to be calm and relaxed.  I try not to let the stress of work or life get to me.   I like to try new things but I have hobby that I truly enjoy like listening to music.

I have a very low level of extroversion and avoid others most of the time, and I prefer working on things by myself. I am higher in agreeableness, since I prefer not to disturb others too much. I am high in conscientiousness since I work hard and tend to follow the rules and have routines. I'm probably moderate in the area of neuroticism since I have a lot of anxiety, particularly when dealing with people. I'm probably lower in openness to experience since I tend to prefer sticking to my routines and having a structured life, although I do consider myself to be relatively curious and creative.

Extroversion: I am not extroverted. I tend to keep to myself and will interact when I am drawn into conversations. Otherwise, I am plenty happy to sit and observe others. 

Agreeableness: I am middle of the road. I can be selfish, but am also very aware of others' feelings and needs. It depends on my mood and which way I go. 

Conscientiousness: I am extremely conscientious. I am a very hard worker, preferring routine and order. I have a creative side and am very happy to figure out the puzzle of new processes. I like to create things and work hard to do so, particularly on time and on budget. 

Neuroticism: I am even keel and mostly unemotional. 

Openness to Experience: I am very open to new experiences. I do so within limits pending my work schedule.

Being social isn't always the most important thing to me. Most of the time, I prefer to be alone and to work on things on my own. I am often polite and careful in what i say. I am often honest and prefer things to be tidy. I'm not often that emotional, but I do react strongly to stress sometimes. It usually depends on what is stressing me out. I often enjoy learning new things. I frequently daydream about things I want to happen.

I live a very social life. I like to organize meetings with friends and family. I really enjoy collaborating with others on projects. I am someone who can be agreeable, especially if I am persuaded by objective facts. I really do not like people who cannot be trusted. One thing all my friends would tell you about me is that I can always be trusted and counted upon. Unlike most people around me, I do not tend to feel threatened or overly moved my situations that are not obviously dire. I like to seek new experiences. I make sure I learn new things often.

I feel like I am an interesting person who likes to keep some privacy and stay in the background to an extent but not so much that I come off as unapproachable. I like to appear calm and in control on the surface but inside I am constantly nervous and worried. People sometimes find me a little intimidating but I easily get almost everyone who talks to me to like me because I can be very friendly and charismatic.

I'm definitely a loner, so bottom of the barrel on Extroversion.
I wouldn't say I'm horribly impolite and dislike people, but I'm definitely blunt and truthful to a fault. So moderately low on Agreeableness.
I don't think I've ever consciously cheated anyone in my life, but my house could definitely stand a deep cleaning. It's hard to judge this one. The house needs cleaning because I have so many other things I need to do, and prioritize everything else, so I'm hardworking. I'm just overworked. So high on Conscientiousness.
Medium high on neuroticism. Don't even have to think about that one.
I'm simultaneously creative, curious, a life-long learner and an Olympic level daydreamer, while also preferring predictability and structure overall. So medium high on Openness to Experience.

I am a multi faceted person. I like my alone time as much as I love being with people. I am a very empathetic person. I want very much to help people as much as I'm able. Because of my faith life which is the most important aspect of my personality, I'm geared towards loving and caring . I am somewhat more comfortable with a routine that doesn't flux much, yet I want to stay open to possibilities. Those are great moments for taming the rigidity I generally prefer.

I am not an extrovert, but I try not to be an introvert as well. I'd just rather mind my own business. I can be agreeable but I seldom have a reason to, and I certainly don't do it for the sake of it. I definitely feel conscientiousness, and I definitely don't think honest and hardworking are the same thing. I am not at all neurotic. There are things I'm sensitive about but I work hard to keep my emotions from getting in the way and most of the time that's easy for me. I'm very open to experiences.

I am usually able to talk to a lot of different people once I warm up to a situation. I am usually shy to start with but warm up quickly. I don't like changing anything about myself to make others more comfortable. I am truthful and have a strong work ethic, although my own home is always a mess. I try not to become emotional in most situations, and it is a self improvement project that seems to always be ongoing. I love doing new things and learning new things and enjoy satisfying my curiosity about the world.

I am an extremely emotional person. I tend to over react to stressful situations. Everything makes me angry these days. I am very honest and work hard.  I believe in personal responsibility above all else, and I don't blame others for my problems or expect help.  I think about things that are happening now or in the past. Those are the only things we can be sure of. Fantasizing is a waste of time reserved for children. I am realistic. I am very polite and tolerant, but I'm about to give up that life time habit because of the total disregard stupid uninformed people have these days, for anyone who doesn't think like them or do as they're told.

If I had to pick one it is going to be openness for myself. I feel like when it comes to me I love putting myself out there in order to experience new things. I always think that for me I love being down to earth. I dont get too up or too down. I am also someone that is extroverted so youd have to say I some extroversion. I love being social and having an active social life.

I like to be by myself and feel complete when I am in silence. I try to suit others needs without losing sight of my own. I like keeping my space clean and organized. I try to stay calm in situations. I have a vivid imagination and daydream a lot, but am not much of an adventurous person.

I prefer to not seek fulfillment from sources outside myself. I prefer to keep to myself. I am typically polite and like people. I adjust my behavior to get along with others. I am honest and hardworking. I follow rules and prefer my house to be clean. I tend to be depressed and anxious. My mood does not change often. I daydream a lot and am curious about the world.

I like to be left alone when working on projects because I like to be in charge and handle the entire responsibility and work flow on my own. I'm a creative thinker and do not like to be held back by other people when completing a job. At the same time, I'm an agreeable person and have a very soft heart. I believe in lifting others up and go to pieces when I hear that there is someone out there who is in need of help. I'm very hard working and do not let the setbacks discourage me from moving forward. I also have big emotions and tend to respond    with much anxiety and irritability when faced with stress, I'm very impressionable and have a strong sense of justice . I'm a very traditional person and place high value on religious faith and traditional family system.

I am a very honest person. I follow rules and am hardworking. I tend to quiet in front of people that I do not know well. I am not a very emotional person I keep my emotions to myself. I need to have a routine and like things to be in order. I am a person who does not like to take risks. I also like to help people in anything that they need. I am also polite to people and don't like confrontations.

i'm sixty six years old and the older i get, the less interested i am in spending time with other people; except for my closest relatives.  fortunately i retired three years ago so i am no longer subjected to useless office chatter.  i consider myself unusually honest, but i am honest with tact.  i don't use being honest as an excuse to make people feel bad.  i doubt there are many people more moody than i am and this is a definite problem that i struggle with.  with rare exceptions, anti-depressants and anti-anxiety medications have been ineffective because of their side effects.  i am not quite a hermit but not far from being one.   in the rare instances when i am with a group of people i will do almost anything to avoid an argument.  life isn't as bad as it may seem but it's far from where i'd like to be on a "scale" of happiness.

I am a person who cares deeply for the people in my life and for those I encounter during my day.  I do not seek out new relationships easily or frequently but I try hard to make sure my friends and family are taken care of and are listened to.  I am happiest doing quiet things like reading and walking with my dog.  But if I am at a party or event I make sure that others feel welcome and included.  My quiet life and self reflection do at times make me sad and a little lonely.  I have to try hard to put myself out there to meet new people.  Despite my solitude I am a great team worker and leader.  I make sure everyone on the team has an opportunity to speak and be heard.  I set an example with my effort and dedication while also making sure each individual on my team feels cared for.

According to Essentials of Organizational Behavior: 14th Edition, the big five personality dimension that has the biggest influence on job performance is conscientiousness. Those who score higher in this trait are likely to have higher levels of job-related knowledge as those who are highly conscientious learn more

I tend to be a quiet person that thinks before they act or speak and I like to work on things by myself. My work is important to me and doing a good job, accurately and consistently is what I strive for. I am always aware of others state of being and always have a certain amount of concern for them, while not being swayed by their state in an emotional way. I like to find and explore new things and learn wherever I can. I do tend to worry quite a bit about many things, yet only when it comes to things that directly affect me.

I think of myself as a person who enjoys being with people, but also appreciates time on my own to think and reflect. I find great satisfaction in my activities and I love to learn new skills. I like to get to know a wide variety of people and I can understand points of view different from my own. I enjoy my comfortable home, but do like to keep things organized. When things don't go my way, I try to take an accepting and optimistic outlook on the situation.

I would describe my personality as rational and adaptable.  I am open to a variety of experiences, and am eager to try out new things.  I am not afraid to take risks, and value the importance of getting out of my comfort zone to confront things that may frighten me.  I can be shy at times, but generally am open to talking to people I've never met before.  I am sympathetic, and will often lend an ear to anyone wishing to talk about their problems.  I am generally emotionally stable and do not let things bother me too much.  All in all, I would describe myself as someone who is open to new experiences, and will often see the good in people.

I would say that I don't like to disagree with the group. I conform to social norms and like to cooperate with others. I am interested in people but I am not that talkative. I like to observe others in their natural environment. I tend to stick with the familiar and like to plan my day. I hate being taken by surprise. I am open to new ideas only if I deem them to be safe and interesting. I feel comfortable around my friends and don't hide my emotions when I'm with them. With strangers or acquaintances, I am much more reserved. I think hardwork gets you far in life and I believe that most people reap what they sow. I love my family, friends and pets very much. I can't image my life without them.

i would consider myself a very open minded person. I am somewhat of free spirit also. I like to march to the beat of my own drum. Letting my imagination run wild is an everyday occurrence for me. Sometimes i get so lost in those thoughts that people have to literally shake me to bring me back. I spend a lot of time inside my mind. It is a happy place for me. I also love learning all kinds of information and learning about people. It intrigues me on we are all connected in some fashion

I am an outgoing and social person but I don't always feel like socializing because I sometimes don't like to leave my familiar surroundings for new things. I will almost always endure various discomforts for a friend or family member in need and my mood is usually calm but a little tense. I do get stressed out or overwhelmed fairly easily, if my routine is disrupted or plans change at the last minute. Or if I feel like I have too many tasks to accomplish in too short a period of time.

I like to keep to myself about 95% of the time, as it feels draining to be around other people, especially energetic people, and I barely have enough energy to get through the day as it is. I prefer it to be quiet and calm so I can focus on my work without extra distractions. That said, I do get along with people quite well and I think people find me friendly, funny, and fun to be around once they get to know me a little bit. I probably come across as a bit mean and intimidating because I don't typically initiate conversations or interactions and have been told I have an intense demeanor. Doing new things is certainly fun and interesting but I typically have so much to do at work or home that I don't get around to doing too much, or necessarily have the money for it.

I think i like to talk to others. I like to get to know people. I find orders interesting to be around.  I think i am easy to get along with. I try to keep track of all the details necessary to get the job done. I don‚Äôt obsess over things. If something goes wrong i don‚Äôt obsess over it.  I love to experience new things and am always looking for a good adventure.  I love to have a good time in life.

I am a very introverted person. I used to be more extroverted but as I got older I was okay staying to myself. As for agreeableness I typically will agree with someone to avoid confrontation. Sometimes it's not worth arguing. I'm conscientious to a point but not at the upper level. I'm definitely not neurotic but I like cleanliness. I'm pretty open to new things as long as they are low risk.

I am very much an introvert. I can be social once I get to know people and enjoy small gatherings with people I know or who maybe friends-of-friends. Large groups tend to bring out my more anxious and self-conscious side. I like to go to new places and try new things (museums, new restaurants, cooking classes, etc). I like to travel and explore (mostly by walking) new cities and cultures. Overall, though, I like my simple life at home and the parts of daily life some others may consider boring, I find comfort in. I do tend to be a little uptight with things like placing items where they belong, when to do certain things, how to do certain things (i.e. dusting the ceiling fan before vacuuming bc it's more efficient, or the proper way to load a dishwasher to maximize the load and reduce the times it has to run. I am currently working on changing this as it's not something I like about myself when it gets to the extreme.
